69th Legislature 2025 HB 124.1
1 HOUSE BILL NO. 124
2 INTRODUCED BY E. ALBUS, E. TILLEMAN, B. LER
3
4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING BICYCLE LAWS; PROVIDING THAT BICYCLES MUST
5 BE RIDDEN OPPOSITE THE FLOW OF TRAFFIC UNLESS RIDDEN WITH A FLAG VEHICLE ESCORT; AND
6 REPEALING SECTIONS 61-8-602 AND 61-8-605, MCA.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Riding on roadways. (1) A person operating a bicycle on a roadway
11 without a flag vehicle escort shall ride opposite the flow of traffic.
12 (2) A person operating a bicycle on a roadway with a flag vehicle escort shall ride with the flow of
13 traffic.
14
15 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Repealer. The following sections of the Montana Code Annotated are
16 repealed:
17 61-8-602. Traffic laws applicable to persons operating bicycles or mopeds.
18 61-8-605. Riding on roadways.
19
20 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Codification instruction. [Section 1] is intended to be codified as an
21 integral part of Title 61, chapter 8, part 6, and the provisions of Title 61, chapter 8, part 6, apply to [section 1].
22 - END -
